          "content": "## Accounting Cycle\nThe accounting cycle records financial transactions step by step.\n\n### Steps\n1. Journal entries\n2. Ledger posting\n3. Trial balance\n\n### Key Rule\nTotal debits must equal total credits.\n\n### Insight\nErrors may still exist even if trial balance matches.",
          "examples": [
            "Recording sales in journal",
            "Posting to ledger accounts"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Wrong classification of accounts",
            "Assuming trial balance guarantees accuracy"
          ],
          "qna": [
            { "q": "What is journal?", "a": "Book of original entry." },
            { "q": "What is ledger?", "a": "Classification of accounts." },
            {
              "q": "What is trial balance?",
              "a": "Check for arithmetic accuracy."
            },
            { "q": "Does trial balance detect all errors?", "a": "No." },
            {
              "q": "Why important?",
              "a": "Foundation for financial statements."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
