          "content": "## Final Accounts\nFinal accounts show profitability and financial position.\n\n### Components\n- **Profit & Loss Account**: Net profit\n- **Balance Sheet**: Assets, liabilities, equity\n\n### Insight\nProfit does not always mean strong cash flow.",
          "examples": [
            "Company reporting profit but low cash",
            "Balance sheet analysis"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Ignoring liabilities",
            "Confusing revenue with profit"
          ],
          "qna": [
            { "q": "What does P&L show?", "a": "Profit or loss." },
            {
              "q": "What does balance sheet show?",
              "a": "Financial position."
            },
            { "q": "Assets?", "a": "Resources owned." },
            { "q": "Liabilities?", "a": "Obligations." },
            { "q": "Key insight?", "a": "Profit ≠ cash." }
          ]
        }
      ]
